            <p>
              Which of the arrow diagrams in <xref ref="fig_arrow61-2">Figure</xref>
              can be used to represent a function from <m>A</m> to <m>B</m>?
              Explain.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p>
              For those arrow diagrams that can be used to represent a function from <m>A</m> to <m>B</m>,
              determine the range of the function.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      <figure xml:id="fig_arrow61-2">
        <caption>Arrow Diagrams</caption>
        <image width="73%" source="images/figps-arrow-exer611abc.png"/>
      </figure>
    </investigation>
    <p>
      \exercises{Exercises 6.1}
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Let <m>f\x \mathbb{R} \to \mathbb{R}</m> be defined by <m>f\left( x \right) = x^2 - 2x</m>.
        </p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p>
              Evaluate <m>f( { - 3} ), f( { - 1} ), f( 1 ), \text{ and } f( 3 )</m>.
            </p>
